intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of this course students will be able to:
Explain a range of advanced practices in software product release engineering including change management, continuous integration and -delivery, software evolution, build automation, and software security;
Reflect critically on the design decisions and trade-offs involved in building and releasing long-lived software products;
Apply and adapt techniques for planning and maintaining up-time and maintenance cycles;
Understand and apply known stability patterns to maintain scaling and software release availability targets;
Design, plan, implement, deploy, maintain and evolve software  releases;
Be aware of the limitations of existing software engineering practices in large scale systems development.
